, "peopleAlsoViewed/24/public_identifier": "watsaphon-intarasongkroaw-9293b9218", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAADbgYPEBzuO_t016zfnlUxWFXPZtA6Vs0A8", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/entity_urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAPl7V8BiyGy77g_g8esoeO1FgzEcWWyemc", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/first_name": "Kanit", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/follower_count": "1581", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/headline": "Country General Manager - Thailand & Laos at The Ascott Limited", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/last_name": "Sangmookda", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/profile_picture": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQEFIqSVt-FBEA/profile-displayphoto-crop_800_800/B56ZnNNa83JkAI-/0/1760084472706?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=m6ZneR0wV0boOicTmbFBNpQLo92XCHsotlKTOWZiEa0", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/public_identifier": "kanit-sangmookda-393a9b19", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAAPl7V8BiyGy77g_g8esoeO1FgzEcWWyemc", "publicIdentifier": "majinder-kaur-ab65bb22", "recommendations/0/context": "Majinder worked with senada on the same team", "recommendations/0/date": "February 7, 2015", "recommendations/0/description": "I had the opportunity to work with Senada for a few months in Paris when I was there for a pre-opening stint from Singapore.  Senada is an independant, committed and resourceful individual.  She is always hungry for business and never hesitates to explore different techniques to clinch the opportunities available to benefit the organization she works for.", "recommendations/0/name": "senada RAMIC", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Director of Sales & Marketing @ DoubleTree by Hilton Luxembourg", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/senada-ramic-b5b1152b/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAY-9TcBqwgNHX6HUHs3QcZqURrkOk4Dwnw", "recommendations/1/context": "Majinder was Alex's client", "recommendations/1/date": "July 6, 2013", "recommendations/1/description": "Alex is a detailed oriented individual.  We hired him and his company to run Breakfast Operations in Pattaya.  I must say we had no qualms at all and follow up was never required.\nHis team was on time everyday and the quality splendid.  Alex was easy to communicate with and dynamic, adapting to changes all the time.\n\nMajinder", "recommendations/1/name": "Alex Chan", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "F&B Professional", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/alex-chan-42145025/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAU6F1kB5mGqFr7QRO-3yEsbq4badOqzb_k", "recommendations/2/context": "Majinder worked with Henry on the same team", "recommendations/2/date": "June 1, 2011", "recommendations/2/description": "Henry is a colleague and friend with full of determination, an excellent communicator and a motivating trainer.\nI had a chance to work with Henry in 2006 when he was assigned to conduct trainings for the Bangkok properties.  He was very engaging and managed to motivate even the rank and file who shy away from speaking English.  At the end of the day, his method of trainings remained on the lips of the employees for a long time to come.\nI will not hesitate to recommend Henry to any company and he will truly be an asset.", "recommendations/2/name": "Henry P.", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Executive Headhunter, Training & Empowerment Consultant, Management & HR Operations Auditor", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/henry-p-96694421/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAASWoF4B0uHh7swL0FtWWKfG-VYYR4ybBHI", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Augustine managed Majinder directly", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "February 7, 2015", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "Majinder Kaur, was employed by Frasers Hospitality Pte Ltd from July 2001 till March 2011, and occupied various positions. \nFrasers Hospitality is a subsidiary of Frasers Centerpoint Ltd, and a member of Fraser and Neave Limited. \n\nMajinder joined Fraser as Events & Proimotions Executive and was responsible for organizing Residents events for both properties in Singapore (Fraser Suites & Fraser Place).\n\nIn 2004, Majinder was promoted and moved to the Headquarters, as part of the Regional Operations Support Team. In her role here, she was given the tasks of pre opening new properties, as well as to provide operational support to existing properties that needs assistance. In her pre opening assignments, she spent 4 months in Fraser Suites Seoul, 4 months in Fraser Place Langsuan and 4 months in Le Caridge, Paris. She was also seconded to Fisherman’s Village Resort, Thailand, as Resort Manager for a year from December 2004. \n\nIn July 2006, she was tasked to be based at Fraser Place Langsuan, as Executive Assistant Manager.  As Executive Assistance Manager, Majinder was responsible for the Rooms Division Departments of the property. These include Front Office, Housekeeping, Security, Engineering Departments, Human Resource and Condo Management .  During this period, Sallin was also utilized to support Frasers Hospitality in pre opening its other properties in Singapore, as well as its first 2 properties overseas, in Seoul and Manila. She reported to an off-site General Manager, on a cluster organization chart.\n\nIn preparation for more responsibilities, Majinder was also put I not a training program on Global Sales & Marketing, to close the gap on her knowledge in this area. Eventually in December 2008, December 2008, Majinder was promoted and given the task to pre-open and manage Fraser Resort Pattaya.   As General Manager, Sallin was responsible for the performance of the property, maintain the fine relationship with Owners and train and develop senior managers to take on larger portfolio. She was successful on all account.    \n\nIn October 2009, after completing her one year assignment in Pattaya, Majinder was moved to Phachara Suites Bangkok, to pre open and manage the “non branded” property. This property was similar to a Fraser Residence, but existing exclusivity arrangements with another partner, did not allow Fraser Hospitality to brand this property a Fraser. \n\nMajinder has always demonstrated professionalism, passion in her work and super relationship with internal and external customers.  Majinder  needs no supervision, an easy person to communicate with, and someone who is always available to all levels of employees. She made her presence felt and was a star in our team.   \n\nAfter much time away, Majinder decided to resign, return back to Singapore for a long overdue rest, before taking on another assignment. We wish her the very best!  \n", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Augustine Silva", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "Hospitality Professional", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/augustinesilva/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAA4HNk8By9mjSLOvdzNvVQAC2uqe2p_Kt7s", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "Christopher managed Majinder directly", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "February 26, 2013", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "I have had the pleasure to have worked with Majinder. Integrity and reliability is high amongst her many virtues. She is very result driven and has sound relationship with her peers as well as earning respect with her staff.\n\nIt will be my greatest pleasure to be able to work with Majinder again.", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Christopher Bong", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Experienced in Serviced Apartments and Hotel Management", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/christopher-bong-6065a410/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAI5BGYB086Gz_6D7f9n0PngTexcD8KIWdk", "skills/0/title": "Analytic Problem Solving", "skills/1/title": "Workable Solutions", "skills/2/title": "Talent Development", "skills/3/title": "Resource Allocation", "skills/4/title": "Project Management", "skills/5/title": "Knowledge Acquisition", "skills/6/title": "S