 with a great pleasure  works with Mr Matthieu Reynaud during many years at vatel silapakorn university Bangkok.\nDuring this years he was of very well advise especially in food and beverage.\nhe very easy approach and  good listening, very pleasant to exchange ideas with him for up quality and to create new menu concept for give the best teaching for the students and for customers come enjoyed the French culinary cooked and prepared by a young Thai generation have a passion of hospitality job. \nAs executive chef I have opportunity often talk with him about my culinary knowledge, whats the best for a chef have a person of front of you for exchange the felling and sensations of the different flavours and senses  of the heritage culinary from my country, also he the man love a good foods so he know the professional way  give the best service and recommendations to the student and the guest [ you can tell only Bon Appetit Mister ] \nI recommend you warmly Mr Matthieu Reynaud a person professional and have  a lot of respect for the hospitality job.\n\nExecutive chef Mr Gilles Poitevin\n", "recommendationsReceived/5/name": "gilles poitevin", "recommendationsReceived/5/subtitle": "executive chef", "recommendationsReceived/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/gilles-poitevin-a0846936/", "recommendationsReceived/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAeK-GgBQgfAJMXglqlFmh5Joui5YafHdPE", "recommendationsReceived/6/context": "Sam reported directly to Matthieu", "recommendationsReceived/6/date": "November 9, 2017", "recommendationsReceived/6/description": "Matthieu is the consummate hotelier whom leads in exemplary fashion and with only 2 goals in mind his guests satisfaction and team development. \n\nMatthieu has a natural talent for stimulating & harnessing his team to deliver above and beyond expectation results something that can only be described as a Midas touch. \n\nI wouldn't need a second thought to work with Matthieu again and the 3+ years together culminated in being the best and most rewarding of my career thus far.  \n\nThank you Matthieu", "recommendationsReceived/6/name": "Sam Ashworth", "recommendationsReceived/6/subtitle": "EAM | Director of Food & Beverage | Luxury | Asia", "recommendationsReceived/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sam-ashworth-b1242222/", "recommendationsReceived/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAASwhb4Bk4STH5Dtz3UnnhZ3VksUvjarCZ8", "recommendationsReceived/7/context": "Adisorn reported directly to Matthieu", "recommendationsReceived/7/date": "November 7, 2017", "recommendationsReceived/7/description": "Dear Khun Matthieu\n\nI thank you all for your kindness, support, and friendship. During working with you at Pathumwan Princess Hotel . You are my great Boss  indeed !! You  always supported me in  the a varieties the difficult times.  With you, I experienced many positive moments I will always remember. I also remember when I have the problem with manpower  also  all staff was happy when you presented chocolate for Christmas time  to everyone. I will always remember every one of you, as you are my great boss and if i have a good chance  i hope to join with you again  with good and happy moments we experienced together.\n\nAdisorn Yothinkamchornchai\nDirector of Housekeeping\n", "recommendationsReceived/7/name": "Adisorn Yothinkamchornchai", "recommendationsReceived/7/subtitle": "Director Of Housekeeping at SIAM KEMPINSKI HOTEL", "recommendationsReceived/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/adisorn-yothinkamchornchai-78088945/", "recommendationsReceived/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAmP-RABTXLyXby0SqPmpIVts8PPXrYks3k", "recommendationsReceived/8/context": "Albert reported directly to Matthieu", "recommendationsReceived/8/date": "November 4, 2017", "recommendationsReceived/8/description": "I have worked under Mr. Reynaud during his time at Pathumwan Princess Hotel in which he has demonstrated his leadership skill by showing the concept  of “leading by example” on day to day basis. Furthermore, he is also an excellent person who possesses excellent creativity whereby helped improve the hotel and brought admirations  from many professions. \n\nWorking under him was much pleasure as his demanding mind-set helped many individuals including myself to  grow even more insult many weaknesses became our expertise.", "recommendationsReceived/8/name": "Albert Phanpiravong", "recommendationsReceived/8/subtitle": "Stay Rewarded!", "recommendationsReceived/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/aphanpiravong/", "recommendationsReceived/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAqMDsABqgLE5TrbphV9WUbsiZjwGKAHdSE", "recommendationsReceived/9/context": "Florian reported directly to Matthieu", "recommendationsReceived/9/date": "April 28, 2016", "recommendationsReceived/9/description": "I had the pleasure to work for Mr. Reynaud on Koh Lanta. He was my GM. \nMr. Reynaud is a true Hospitality leader with a big heart for the whole team. \nprofessional and polite Mr. Reynaud taught me a lot for my future career path wich I will always remember. I would work with Mr. Reynaud anytime again. ", "recommendationsReceived/9/name": "Florian Winkler", "recommendationsReceived/9/subtitle": "Business Development Lead | Franchise Development, Lead Aquisition, Mergers & Acquisitions, International Development | QSR Expert | VP Level - C Suite Level Developing great brands across EMEA & APAC", "recommendationsReceived/9/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/florian-winkler-2b2a0b21/", "recommendationsReceived/9/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAASZU-YBEj8z2L7akKBxhav2CxHwW8ZI7h0", "recommendationsReceived/10/context": "Yenon was Matthieu's client", "recommendationsReceived/10/date": "February 10, 2016", "recommendationsReceived/10/description": "I write this pleasurable recommendations on yourself, and your management style. As I have previously mentioned to your senior, you have a wonderful ability to let every guest feel special, and that you honestly care for each and every one of them. \nOne of the main reasons 